<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-1407] debian init script could be more consistent w/ bin/cassandra</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1407</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the introduction of conf/cassandra-env.sh it should be possible to eliminate the separately maintained /etc/default/cassandra.  The init script should also use a JAVA_HOME derived from the java binary in PATH (if it exists), both because this is how things work in Debian (&lt;em&gt;the&lt;/em&gt; Java is the one chosen by alternatives), and because this is how bin/cassandra works as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patches to follow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
